00:39:59,000 --> 00:40:01,128
Am I the only sane person
left on this planet?

765
00:40:01,200 --> 00:40:04,249
I love him, but he was always
an incorrigible child.

766
00:40:04,320 --> 00:40:05,526
Can I give you something?

767
00:40:05,600 --> 00:40:07,600
No, thank you. Just a little
wine, if you have any.

768
00:40:07,640 --> 00:40:08,846
We've just eaten.

769
00:40:08,920 --> 00:40:10,081
Oh, are those
little cakes?

770
00:40:10,160 --> 00:40:12,766
Good heavens, are you seriously
going to have more food?

771
00:40:12,840 --> 00:40:13,966
They're delicious.

772
00:40:14,040 --> 00:40:15,087
Unbelievable!

773
00:40:15,160 --> 00:40:18,209
Now, tell me something about my
Aunt Vanessa's colorful past.

774
00:40:18,280 --> 00:40:19,964
Oh, leave her alone,
Stanley.

775
00:40:20,040 --> 00:40:21,963
She's not
a performing monkey.

776
00:40:22,040 --> 00:40:24,281
Do you have a telephone
I could use?

777
00:40:24,400 --> 00:40:27,165
I'm sorry, it's 3:00, and I was
supposed to meet Brice for drinks,

778
00:40:27,240 --> 00:40:28,366
but I'm never
gonna make it.

779
00:40:28,440 --> 00:40:31,330
Brice Catledge is the young
milksop who's smitten with her,

780
00:40:31,400 --> 00:40:33,482
and ready to lay his
family fortune at her feet

781
00:40:33,560 --> 00:40:35,289
to subsidize
her chicanery.

782
00:40:35,360 --> 00:40:37,328
Can you believe it?
He serenades her.

783
00:40:37,400 --> 00:40:38,765
Well, it sounds
rather romantic to me,

784
00:40:38,840 --> 00:40:40,922
but you wouldn't know
about such things, Stanley.

785
00:40:41,040 --> 00:40:43,008
It would mean
joining the human race.

786
00:40:43,080 --> 00:40:46,084
Here, it's in the study.
Thank you.

787
00:40:46,160 --> 00:40:47,764
Why do you badger her?

788
00:40:47,880 --> 00:40:50,850
She's quite likable,
even if she is a fraud.

789
00:40:50,920 --> 00:40:53,969
You know, one of the
cardinal rules of magic,

790
00:40:54,040 --> 00:40:56,247
is that the magician
must never repeat his trick,

791
00:40:56,320 --> 00:40:58,800
because sooner or later, one
begins to notice the move,

792
00:40:58,880 --> 00:41:01,201
and he's caught.

793
00:41:01,320 --> 00:41:03,891
But the more I watch her... Yes?

794
00:41:05,880 --> 00:41:08,042
The more I'm stumped.

795
00:41:11,680 --> 00:41:13,762
Could she be real?

796
00:41:13,920 --> 00:41:15,160
(QUIET LAUGH)

797
00:41:15,240 --> 00:41:17,322
I'm beginning to question
my own common sense.

798
00:41:17,560 --> 00:41:19,801
I've always questioned
your common sense.

799
00:41:19,880 --> 00:41:23,168
You've always been so certain
about the world, Stanley.

800
00:41:23,240 --> 00:41:26,005
And I've always tried to teach
you that we don't know.

801
00:41:26,080 --> 00:41:28,367
We really don't know.

802
00:41:28,440 --> 00:41:32,206
We're just poor,
limited human beings.

803
00:41:32,280 --> 00:41:33,964
The goldfish
doesn't understand

804
00:41:34,040 --> 00:41:35,610
who changes
the water in his bowl.

805
00:41:35,920 --> 00:41:37,843
If only she was real,

806
00:41:37,920 --> 00:41:39,251
it would lift
the dark cloud

807
00:41:39,320 --> 00:41:40,446
that's followed me
since childhood.

808
00:41:40,560 --> 00:41:43,723
Well, I'm sure your fiancée would
appreciate a sunnier bridegroom.

809
00:41:43,800 --> 00:41:47,441
Olivia likes me as I am. Sophie
agrees we're a match made in heaven.

810
00:41:47,520 --> 00:41:49,249
Has she met her?

811
00:41:50,320 --> 00:41:53,802
No, but there,
she's guessing correctly.

812
00:41:53,880 --> 00:41:55,644
I told Brice I'd be late.

813
00:41:55,720 --> 00:41:58,530
I said I was just sitting down
for some of your blood pudding.

814
00:41:58,600 --> 00:42:01,922
Tell me something
about my aunt.

815
00:42:04,480 --> 00:42:07,802
Do you have
a, uh, handkerchief

816
00:42:07,920 --> 00:42:10,366
or an article
of clothing,

817
00:42:10,440 --> 00:42:12,442
or a piece of jewelry
I could use?

818
00:42:12,520 --> 00:42:14,522
Oh, my pearls.

819
00:42:23,280 --> 00:42:25,487
These are beautiful.

820
00:42:26,080 --> 00:42:27,525
<i>(CLEARS THROAT)</i>

