00:42:40,400 --> 00:42:41,765
Cloudy...

827
00:42:41,840 --> 00:42:45,367
Here comes the usual
theatrical fertilizer.

828
00:42:47,200 --> 00:42:48,690
(STANLEY SIGHS)

829
00:42:51,480 --> 00:42:54,165
I see an important Englishman.
(STANLEY SCOFFS)

830
00:42:58,480 --> 00:43:01,484
Perhaps a member
of Parliament.

831
00:43:02,440 --> 00:43:04,010
Go on.

832
00:43:06,680 --> 00:43:07,806
A love affair.

833
00:43:07,880 --> 00:43:09,040
STANLEY:
I don't believe this.

834
00:43:09,080 --> 00:43:12,607
You cannot
possibly know this.

835
00:43:12,680 --> 00:43:14,444
Something's wrong.

836
00:43:14,520 --> 00:43:15,931
STANLEY: What?

837
00:43:16,000 --> 00:43:17,445
He's married.

838
00:43:17,520 --> 00:43:18,851
Aunt Vanessa?

839
00:43:18,920 --> 00:43:20,126
I see a sequence
of trysts.

840
00:43:20,240 --> 00:43:21,366
I've never
told her anything.

841
00:43:21,440 --> 00:43:22,930
He cannot leave
his wife.

842
00:43:23,000 --> 00:43:24,650
No, he did not.

843
00:43:24,720 --> 00:43:26,563
And so,
you're heartbroken.

844
00:43:26,640 --> 00:43:27,766
Sophie, you are a miracle.

845
00:43:27,840 --> 00:43:29,365
And you vow
never to love again.

846
00:43:29,440 --> 00:43:30,646
How does she do it?

847
00:43:30,720 --> 00:43:33,007
You're never to marry.

848
00:43:33,080 --> 00:43:35,242
This is beyond comprehension. I've
never known anything like it...

849
00:43:35,320 --> 00:43:37,368
But this is a symbol.
This is...

850
00:43:37,880 --> 00:43:39,723
The breakup.

851
00:43:39,800 --> 00:43:44,283
He gave me those
on our last evening together.

852
00:43:44,400 --> 00:43:46,164
Sophie.
I'm so sorry.

853
00:43:46,240 --> 00:43:48,288
Sophie, is there
really a spirit world?

854
00:43:48,360 --> 00:43:49,930
Do you really tune in
on it?

855
00:43:50,000 --> 00:43:52,651
Is there more?
Have I not seen it?

856
00:43:52,720 --> 00:43:54,370
Where have you
been all my life?

857
00:43:54,440 --> 00:43:55,441
(♪♪♪)

858
00:44:01,880 --> 00:44:05,566
When did you first realize you
had this extraordinary gift?

859
00:44:05,640 --> 00:44:08,610
Oh, uh, very young.
My... My teens.

860
00:44:08,680 --> 00:44:11,729
Well, and you saw it
as a way to make money?

861
00:44:11,800 --> 00:44:15,282
Well, my father abandoned
us, and we were very poor.

862
00:44:15,360 --> 00:44:16,691
Eh, but it's astounding.

863
00:44:16,760 --> 00:44:19,604
I mean, I've always
believed that the dull,

864
00:44:19,680 --> 00:44:22,490
tragic reality of life
is all there is,

865
00:44:22,560 --> 00:44:24,164
but you are proof
that there's more.

866
00:44:24,240 --> 00:44:25,844
More what?

867
00:44:25,920 --> 00:44:30,005
More mystery, more magic.

868
00:44:30,080 --> 00:44:31,206
(ENGINE GRINDING)

869
00:44:31,280 --> 00:44:32,645
Oh, will you...
Oh.

870
00:44:32,720 --> 00:44:34,006
Oh, dear.

871
00:44:34,080 --> 00:44:35,889
Oh, boy.

872
00:44:35,960 --> 00:44:37,644
You leave this to me.

873
00:44:37,720 --> 00:44:39,529
I did get a little
anxious vibration

874
00:44:39,600 --> 00:44:41,364
when the engine
started smoking back there.

875
00:44:41,440 --> 00:44:44,091
Don't worry, I'm gonna
have a look at this.

876
00:44:44,200 --> 00:44:46,931
I actually have an inkling
as to what this might be.

877
00:44:47,000 --> 00:44:49,446
What are you gonna do?

878
00:44:49,520 --> 00:44:51,682
Yes, not to worry.
I think it's the, um...

879
00:44:51,760 --> 00:44:53,171
I'm actually...

880
00:44:53,240 --> 00:44:56,369
I'm actually rather good at
dealing with anything mechanical.

881
00:44:56,760 --> 00:44:57,761
I don't understand it!

882
